          CCaatt reads each file in the order given and writes it to
          the standard output. Thus,
          
                                 ccaatt ffiillee
          
          prints the file and
          
                          ccaatt ffiillee11 ffiillee22 >> ffiillee33
          
          concatenates  the first two files and places the result
          in the third. If no files are given or if "-" is  given
          as  a  file name, ccaatt reads the standard input up to an
          end-of-file.
          
          If the --nn option is given, the lines are numbered.
          
          
